          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-9184 lov: component layout entry can be not just RAID0",
        "message": "LU-9184 lov: component layout entry can be not just RAID0\n\nCurrent implementation of component layout works entries as\nwith RAID0 type always, meanwhile component entry may be\nnot RAID0, e.g. Data-on-MDT type or any other.\nPatch modifies component layout to work with any entry type\nby defining per-entry set of operations by its type.\n\nSigned-off-by: Mikhal Pershin <mike.pershin@intel.com>\nChange-Id: If5ca488e066216584e91c02106722af9afb69850\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
